703417f-c.text:
1) Buswick Ave, south side at adjoining and east of Kossuth Place, formerly the Abraham De Bevoise farmhouse: it was once a family house, but was later converted into a two family dwelling.  In 1869 it was occupied by James De Bevoise.

March 1923

2) The same, another view

March 1923

3) The same, showing the rear and side of the house on Kossuth Place.  At the left, is seen a segment of the Bushwick Ave Reformed Church.

March 1923
